  "texts": [
    "The full prompts are shown in Appendix A.13 LLAMA3.1-AEGISGUARD models output re-sponses in JSON format with up to 3 fields: a prompt safety label, a response safety label, and a list of comma-separated categories based on the AEGIS2.0 taxonomy.",
    "A sample response is {\"User Safety\": \"safe\", \"Response Safety\": \"unsafe\", \"Safety Categories\": \"Violence,Threat\"}.",
    "Note that during training data creation, the response safety categories will only include the categories included in the system prompt.",
    "The remaining are caught by Other.",
    "This means that for the catlist style prompt, the response format would convert fine-grained risks to Other, whereas, it would keep all as-is with catlist+."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}